---
title: Mild & Creamy Fish Curry with Toasted Coconut and Rice
description: This curry doesn't bite! Its north Indian spice is tempered by a creamy sauce which goes perfectly with tender fish and flavoursome veggies. Golden toasted coconut emphasises the sweet notes and it's all served with fragrant basmati rice. Nothing to be afraid of!
image: https://img.hellofresh.com/f_auto,fl_lossy,h_640,q_auto,w_1200/hellofresh_s3/image/mild-creamy-fish-curry-c0f94692-8c5d74f3.jpg
pdf: https://www.hellofresh.co.uk/recipecards/card/mild-creamy-fish-curry-59022a5bc6243b0a695d9612-d0e332a8.pdf
author: Mimi Morley
time required: 35 minutes
nutrition:
  calories: 601 kcal
  fat: 22 g
  saturated fat: 13 g
  carbohydrates: 77 g
  sugar: 12 g
  protein: 29 g
  sodium: 1 g
  serving size: 447
cuisine: Indian
servings: 2
source: https://www.hellofresh.co.uk/recipes/mild-creamy-fish-curry-59022a5bc6243b0a695d9612
course: main course
---

Halve, peel and chop the @onion{1}(peeled and chopped) into roughly ½cm pieces. Peel and grate the @garlic{1%clove} (or use a #garlic press{}). Halve, then remove the core from the @red bell pepper{½}(chopped into 1cm pieces). Pick the @coriander{1}(leaves picked and roughly chopped, stalks finely chopped) and roughly chop. Chop the @smoked fish mix{215%g}(chopped into roughly 2cm pieces) into pieces, leaving the prawns whole.

Put a large #frying pan{} on medium heat and add the @desiccated coconut{12.5%g} (no oil!). Toast until golden, shaking the pan frequently, ~{2-3%minutes}. Then remove to a #bowl{}.

> TIP: Watch it like hawk… you don't want to burn it! Don't wash the pan, we'll use it again.

Pour the @water{300%ml} into a large #saucepan{}. Add a large pinch of @salt{large pinch} and the @cardamom pod{½}. Bring to the boil and add the @basmati rice{150%g}. Pop a #lid{} on and turn the heat to medium-low. Cook for ~{10%minutes}, then remove from the heat and set aside (still covered) for another ~{10%minutes}.

> TIP: The rice will finish cooking in its own steam.

Wipe out your frying pan and pop back on medium heat. Add a drizzle of @oil{drizzle} and the onion. Cook until softened, stirring frequently, ~{5%minutes}. Then add the pepper. Season with a pinch of @salt{pinch} and @black pepper{pinch}. Cook, stirring frequently until the pepper is soft, ~{5%minutes} more. Add the garlic, coriander stalks and @North Indian style spice mix{½%tbsp}.

> Don't add all the spice if you don't like it too hot.

Stir and cook for another ~{1%minute}.

Pour in the @finely chopped tomatoes{½}(diced), @water{50%ml}, and @vegetable stock powder{½%stock pot}. Stir together and bring to a gentle simmer. Cook, stirring frequently for ~{7%minutes}, then pour in the @crème fraîche{75%g}. Gently add the fish mix and submerge in the sauce. Reduce the heat to medium-low, cover with a lid and leave the fish to poach, ~{7%minutes}.

> TIP: The fish is cooked when the centre is opaque. Don't stir or you will break up the fish!

Remove the cardamom pods from the rice (they should be sitting on top) and fluff it up with a #fork{}. Stir half the desiccated coconut through the rice (or leave some of the rice plain for the children if you think they would prefer it like that). Serve the rice in #bowls{} with a good spoonful of fish curry on top and a scattering of toasted coconut and coriander leaves to finish for anyone that wants it. Enjoy!